examples.en: The queen summoned him back to the palace.
Robert summoned the waiter for the bill.
We were summoned to the director's office.
He summoned the waiter with a motion of his hand.
The great bell of St. Paul's was the tocsin which summoned the citizens to arms.
Running into an old friend summoned up memories of her childhood.
He was summoned to attend an emergency meeting.
Absent officers were summoned to join their corps.
Hugh was summoned to appear before the magistrate.
Presently Larry was summoned to help draft the sheep.
Without explanation, the managing editor summoned me to his office.
He summoned a meeting of business leaders.
The president summoned Taylor to Washington.
